Jake Long is a professional team roper from Coffeyville, Kansas, who has made a significant impact in the world of rodeo. He joined the Professional Rodeo Cowboys Association (PRCA) in 2003 and has since amassed over $2 million in earnings, placing him in a rare group of successful ProRodeo competitors.

Here we have Jake Long’s net worth, career earnings, professional career, achievements, relationship status, and more.

About Jake Long

Jake Long was born and raised in Coffeyville, Kansas. He joined the Professional Rodeo Cowboys Association (PRCA) in 2003 and has since become a 12-time Wrangler National Finals Rodeo Qualifier. His consistent performances and dedication to the sport have earned him a significant place in the rodeo world.

Off the rodeo circuit, Long is a family man. He and his wife, Tasha, have two daughters, Haven and Haizlee.

Early Life

Growing up in Kansas, Long was exposed to the cowboy lifestyle from a young age. His passion for rodeo was evident early on, and he quickly developed the skills necessary to compete at a professional level.

Professional Career

Long has qualified for the Wrangler National Finals Rodeo (NFR) 12 times. His career highlights include standing 3rd in the world in 2016, earning $225,091 for the year.

In 2021, he heeled for Clay Tryan and won $199,062, which helped him cross the $2 million mark in career earnings. In 2023, Long continued to demonstrate his skills and resilience. Despite dealing with a broken foot, he continued to compete and succeed.

Alongside Clay Smith, he started the 2023 rodeo season with back-to-back wins in Texas and Colorado. They clinched their second major rodeo title of 2023 with a decisive win at the National Western Stock Show and Rodeo in Denver, Colorado, earning $6,822 per man.

Long’s success is not only due to his skills but also his horses. He rode three-time AQHA/PRCA Heel Horse of the Year Zans Colonel Shine for a significant part of his career, attributing over a million of his earnings to this horse.

Jake Long’s Net Worth in 2023

As of 2023, Jake Long’s net worth is estimated to be around $5 million. This wealth has been accumulated through his successful career as a professional rodeo cowboy.

Career Earnings

Long’s earnings have been consistent throughout his career. In 2016, he stood 3rd in the world, earning $225,091 for the year.

In 2021, he heeled for Clay Tryan and won $199,062, which helped him cross the $2 million mark in career earnings. His professional rodeo career earnings were reported to be $2.05 million, in 2022. As of 2023, his career earnings are $2,225,327.

Personal Details

Wife

Tasha Long is the wife of professional team roper Jake Long. They got married in August 2005. Both Tasha and Jake graduated from Northwestern Oklahoma State University in Alva.

Together, they have two daughters, Haven, born on June 9, 2008, and Haizlee.

How old is he?

Jake Long, the professional rodeo cowboy, is 39 years old as of 2023.

How tall is he?

He is 6 ft tall.

What is his nationality?

He is of American nationality.

Career Stats

  • Jake Long has qualified for the Wrangler National Finals Rodeo 12 times.
  • He joined the Professional Rodeo Cowboys Association (PRCA) in 2003.
  • Long has amassed more than $2 million in Professional Rodeo Cowboy Association earnings since joining the association in 2003.
  • In 2016, he stood 3rd in the world, earning $225,091 for the year.
  • He won the RODEOHOUSTON (Texas) and the Pony Express Rodeo (Eagle Mountain, Utah) in 2023.
  • He also won the Dodge City Roundup Championship in 2022.

FAQs About Jake Long

Estimated $5 million as of 2023.

Coffeyville, Kansas.

In 2003 when he joined the PRCA.

Tasha Long.
